    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Sanford</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Hunter</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 267.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I desire to supply an omission in my despatch No.
                    257.</p>
                <p>The compliments of condolence and of sympathy addressed to me on the part of the
                    King, as I have since learned from his aide-de-camp, applied also to the crime
                    which nearly cost to the state the life of Secretary Seward.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H. S. SANFORD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William Hunter,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
